end of the golden weather
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:[Transf. use of the title of Bruce Mason's monologue celebrating the end of NewZealand childhood innocence.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:also golden weather
Pronunciation:
Notes: New Zealandism
