Vol / Page: 38
Edition:
Quote: The title of <i>The End of the Golden Weather</i> came from Thomas Wolfe's novel, <i>The Web and the Rock</i>, and its content is a gentle exploration of the secretive pleasures and pains of a twelve-year-old boy approaching puberty. <i>Ibid.</i> 39 Although the golden weather of boyhood is marred and effectively ended by the riots, its concomitants linger on into 'Christmas at Te Parenga', the season of ritual indulgence for children.
