Quote: The end of the golden weather - the phrase is endearingly familiar. Freighted with nostalgia, it evokes the days of seemingly endless childhood summers before the cares of adolescence and adulthood arose. Originally the title of a solo stage play, it has passed into our language, lodged there by the man who wrote the play and performed it all over the country for the best part of two decades - the great writer and actor Bruce Mason.
